  <h4 class="accordion-toggle">What is a competency tree / competency tree</h4>
  <div class="accordion-content">
    <p>A skill tree, or competency tree, is a visual hierarchical representation of knowledge.
    Popularized as the technology trees in Civilization and strategy games and Role-Playing Games, they define paths to develop knowledge.
    One interest of those tree is that they provide steps allowing guided and progressive acquisition of knowledge.
    Another popular resource using a skill tree is <a href='duolingo.com'>Duolingo</a>, where the user follows the tree from beginner to fluency
    in a foreign language.</p>
  </div>
  <h4 class="accordion-toggle">Limitation of skill trees</h4>
  <div class="accordion-content">
    <p>Skill trees have several limitations.</p>
    <p>The nature of representation or conceptualization is to simplify a more complex reality.
    Many different representations of one branch of knowledge are posible: we can imagine decomposing the art of cooking in 5, or 10, or 100 different steps.</p>
    <p>Furthermore, it is always posible to know more than the tree is showing, mastering more one competency, getting further. Skill trees are by no mean exhaustive.</p>
  </div><hr>
  <h3>Creating trees</h3>
